{
  "dialogueGraphs": [
    {
      "id": "SCN015_WALL_PHONE_LIST",
      "sceneId": "SCN-015",
      "startNodeId": "INTRO_1",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "INTRO_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The wall phone list is laminated and warped, like it\u2019s been steamed for years. (pause) Too close to other people\u2019s problems. (pause) Most entries are crossed out in pen that\u2019s had time to become policy.",
          "next": "INTRO_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "INTRO_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A strip of new tape sits over a column. The adhesive is clear, not aged.",
          "next": "MENU_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_MAIN",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LOOK_LEGAL",
              "text": "look: Scan for Legal.",
              "next": "LOOK_LEGAL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_REST",
              "text": "look: Look over the rest of the list.",
              "next": "LOOK_REST_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_CALL",
              "text": "use: Use the wall phone to call the Legal extension.",
              "next": "CALL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_COPY_COMMIT",
              "text": "use: Copy down the Legal extension.",
              "next": "COMMIT_COPY_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_PRINT_ADDENDUM",
              "text": "ask: Ask the kiosk to print an approved contact addendum.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "player.factions",
                  "op": "in",
                  "value": [
                    "OLEA"
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "next": "PRINT_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Step away from the list.",
              "next": "END_LEAVE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "LOOK_LEGAL_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Legal.",
          "next": "LOOK_LEGAL_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "LOOK_LEGAL_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You find it twice. \u201cCounsel.\u201d \u201cIncident Containment (Administrative).\u201d Same extension. Someone wanted it to survive edits.",
          "next": "LOOK_LEGAL_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "LOOK_LEGAL_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The Legal line is in a newer font. A quiet update: \u201cWe will be consulted.\u201d",
          "next": "MENU_LEGAL"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_LEGAL",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COPY_FROM_LEGAL",
              "text": "use: Copy down the Legal extension.",
              "next": "COMMIT_COPY_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_CALL_FROM_LEGAL",
              "text": "use: Call the Legal extension.",
              "next": "CALL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_REST_FROM_LEGAL",
              "text": "look: Look over the rest of the list.",
              "next": "LOOK_REST_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_MAIN",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "MENU_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "LOOK_REST_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Facilities routes to a number with an asterisk\u2014no explanation. (pause) Safety has three extensions, each labeled \u201cPRIMARY.\u201d",
          "next": "LOOK_REST_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "LOOK_REST_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Procurement sits under a department name that reads like a confession. Only Legal looks maintained.",
          "next": "MENU_REST"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_REST",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COPY_FROM_REST",
              "text": "use: Copy down the Legal extension.",
              "next": "COMMIT_COPY_2"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_CALL_FROM_REST",
              "text": "use: Call the Legal extension.",
              "next": "CALL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_MAIN_2",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "MENU_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The wall phone\u2019s handset is slightly tacky, the way only public plastic gets. (pause) The dial tone arrives immediately, like it\u2019s been waiting to be useful.",
          "next": "CALL_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The line connects with a click that sounds too modern for this building.",
          "next": "CALL_LEGAL_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_LEGAL_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "LEGAL",
          "text": "Office of Legal Energy Assets, Counsel intake. This line is for procedural clarification only\u2014only\u2014and does not constitute authorization, approval, or a request for action.",
          "next": "CALL_LEGAL_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_LEGAL_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "LEGAL",
          "text": "If you are calling about \u201cclosure,\u201d please note: closure is a fiscal classification, not a physical condition. If you are calling about a physical condition, you are calling the wrong department, for everyone\u2019s benefit.",
          "next": "CALL_LEGAL_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_LEGAL_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "LEGAL",
          "text": "If you need someone to cite, cite \u201cCounsel Intake, extension listed.\u201d Do not cite a name. Names become invitations.",
          "next": "CALL_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The message ends cleanly. No option to leave a voicemail. The extension, at least, is real.",
          "next": "MENU_CALL"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_CALL",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COPY_AFTER_CALL",
              "text": "use: Copy down the Legal extension.",
              "next": "COMMIT_COPY_AFTER_CALL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_MAIN_3",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "MENU_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRINT_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The lobby kiosk wakes with a fan noise that sounds irritated to be involved. (pause) Its screen offers a familiar OLEA header and an unfamiliar warning footer.",
          "next": "PRINT_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "PRINT_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "KIOSK",
          "text": "CONTACT ADDENDUM (INTERNAL REFERENCE). This document is not a directory. This document is not a recommendation.",
          "next": "PRINT_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "PRINT_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "KIOSK",
          "text": "Select contact to append to closure packet:",
          "next": "PRINT_4"
        },
        {
          "id": "PRINT_4",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Legal appears as the first suggestion, like it was already expecting to be attached.",
          "next": "MENU_PRINT"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_PRINT",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_APPEND_PRINT_COMMIT",
              "text": "use: Append Legal extension and print.",
              "next": "COMMIT_PRINT_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_MAIN_4",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "MENU_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "COMMIT_COPY_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You write the extension exactly as shown, prefix nobody uses. Your handwriting stays neat on purpose.",
          "next": "END_NOTE_LEGAL_EXTENSION"
        },
        {
          "id": "COMMIT_COPY_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You add the extension to your working contacts\u2014an escalation channel, a supervisor reference. (pause) Like writing down a fire exit you hope you don\u2019t need.",
          "next": "END_NOTE_LEGAL_EXTENSION"
        },
        {
          "id": "COMMIT_COPY_AFTER_CALL_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You record the extension as a usable escalation channel, per Legal. (pause) It stays impersonal and citable, hard to argue with later. (pause) The paper trail gets heavier. That's the point.",
          "next": "END_NOTE_LEGAL_EXTENSION"
        },
        {
          "id": "COMMIT_PRINT_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The kiosk prints a single strip of paper with the Legal extension and a timestamp. (pause) The font is official enough to be believed and cheap enough to be denied.",
          "next": "END_NOTE_LEGAL_EXTENSION"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_NOTE_LEGAL_EXTENSION",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "note_legal_extension",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "paperwork.legalExtensionNoted",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "paperwork.legalExtension",
              "action": "set",
              "value": "OLEA_LEGAL_EXTENSION"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "END_LEAVE",
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}